# DaisyUI Styling & Theme Integration

This project uses **DaisyUI** with **TailwindCSS** and implements a dual-theme system.

## Theme Configuration

Defined in [global.css](mdc:src/styles/global.css):
```css
@plugin "daisyui" {
  themes:
    silk --default,
    abyss --prefersdark;
}
```

### Theme Usage Rules
- **Light theme**: `silk` (default)
- **Dark theme**: `abyss` (auto-applies with `prefers-color-scheme: dark`)
- **Always use semantic color classes** for theme compatibility

## DaisyUI Component Patterns

### Card Components (Primary Pattern)
```tsx
// Main card structure - used in WidgetCard.tsx
<div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg aspect-square">
  <div class="card-body h-full flex flex-col p-4">
    <h2 class="card-title text-lg font-semibold mb-3 flex-shrink-0">
      {title}
    </h2>
    <div class="flex-1 overflow-y-auto overflow-x-hidden">
      {content}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Form Elements
```tsx
// Input fields
<input class="input input-bordered w-full" />

// Buttons
<button class="btn btn-primary">Primary Action</button>
<button class="btn btn-secondary">Secondary Action</button>
<button class="btn btn-outline">Outline Button</button>

// Textareas
<textarea class="textarea textarea-bordered w-full h-32" />
```

### Layout Components
```tsx
// Headers with consistent styling
<header class="bg-base-100 shadow-sm border-b border-base-300">

// Main content areas
<main class="container mx-auto px-6 py-8">

// Background colors
<div class="min-h-screen bg-base-200">
```

## Semantic Color Classes

### Background Colors
- `bg-base-100` - Primary background (cards, headers)
- `bg-base-200` - Secondary background (page background)
- `bg-base-300` - Tertiary background (borders, dividers)

### Text Colors
- `text-base-content` - Primary text
- `text-base-content/70` - Secondary text (70% opacity)
- `text-base-content/40` - Muted text (40% opacity)

### Border Colors
- `border-base-300` - Standard borders
- `border-base-content/20` - Subtle borders

## Component Styling Standards

### Widget Cards
Must follow this exact structure:
```tsx
<div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg aspect-square">
  <div class="card-body h-full flex flex-col p-4">
    {/* Title area - fixed height */}
    <h2 class="card-title text-lg font-semibold mb-3 flex-shrink-0">
      {title}
    </h2>
    
    {/* Scrollable content area - flexible height */}
    <div class="flex-1 overflow-y-auto overflow-x-hidden">
      {children}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Interactive Elements
```tsx
// Hover states
<button class="btn btn-primary hover:btn-primary-focus">

// Focus states (automatically handled by DaisyUI)
<input class="input input-bordered focus:input-primary" />

// Disabled states
<button class="btn btn-disabled" disabled>
```

## Spacing & Layout Conventions

### Standard Spacing Scale
- **Container padding**: `px-6 py-8` (main content areas)
- **Card padding**: `p-4` (inside card-body)
- **Element gaps**: `gap-6` (between grid items)
- **Content spacing**: `space-y-4` (between form elements)

### Flex Patterns
```tsx
// Card content layout
<div class="h-full flex flex-col space-y-4">

// Center content
<div class="h-full flex items-center justify-center">

// Header layout
<div class="flex items-center justify-between">
```

## Shadow & Visual Hierarchy

### Shadow Levels
- **Cards**: `shadow-lg` (main widget cards)
- **Header**: `shadow-sm` (subtle header shadow)
- **Modals/Overlays**: `shadow-xl` (if needed)

### Visual States
```tsx
// Placeholder/disabled widgets
<div class="opacity-50">

// Loading states
<div class="loading loading-spinner loading-lg">

// Success/error states
<div class="alert alert-success">
<div class="alert alert-error">
```

## Responsive DaisyUI Usage

### Component Responsiveness
DaisyUI components are responsive by default, but combine with Tailwind utilities:

```tsx
// Responsive button sizing
<button class="btn w-full lg:w-auto">

// Responsive modal sizing
<div class="modal-box w-full max-w-2xl">

// Responsive navigation
<div class="navbar lg:navbar-horizontal">
```